{
  "text": "This will enable forensic investigators to collect computer activity data samples from Linux operating system. These details can then be investigated for research. The traditional computer forensics investigative methodology is both time taking and costly in terms of human resources and laboratory software and hardware [CITATION_1] . The acquisition of data from storage media post-mortem poses critical efficiency problems for investigators, as the size of computer storage media increases corresponding with an expansion of computer related activities. So the proposed way seems to be helpful.",
